47943b722c8d151b8d2f8/8bd51/slides-4.jpg 1180w,\n/static/fa71f86f01147943b722c8d151b8d2f8/a3716/slides-4.jpg 1770w,\n/static/fa71f86f01147943b722c8d151b8d2f8/6b37f/slides-4.jpg 4000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n  </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"slides 5\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/ca545/slides-5.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/aa1b7/slides-5.jpg 148w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/b937a/slides-5.jpg 295w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/ca545/slides-5.jpg 590w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/75639/slides-5.jpg 885w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/8bd51/slides-5.jpg 1180w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/a3716/slides-5.jpg 1770w,\n/static/cf7a88c37527f9264de0e3f90b459dff/6b37f/slides-5.jpg 4000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n  </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"slides 6\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/ca545/slides-6.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/aa1b7/slides-6.jpg 148w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/b937a/slides-6.jpg 295w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/ca545/slides-6.jpg 590w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/75639/slides-6.jpg 885w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/8bd51/slides-6.jpg 1180w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/a3716/slides-6.jpg 1770w,\n/static/828979407cab73cf8aa64494c2d72a2d/6b37f/slides-6.jpg 4000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n  </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"slides 8\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/ca545/slides-8.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/aa1b7/slides-8.jpg 148w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/b937a/slides-8.jpg 295w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/ca545/slides-8.jpg 590w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/75639/slides-8.jpg 885w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/8bd51/slides-8.jpg 1180w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/a3716/slides-8.jpg 1770w,\n/static/1fca811c95f3e6ef56f60a116c95cf96/6b37f/slides-8.jpg 4000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n  </span></p>\n<h2>Overview</h2>\n<p>Over the years, our understanding of the world of front end development has changed. We have been iterating constantly on our working theory of how to design and code for the web.</p>\n<p>Weâ€™ve used the tools we have not just to create solutions to the problems we face, but also to create new tools. These tools arenâ€™t just helping us do our job; they are <em>changing</em> the way we can even <em>conceptualize</em> our work. Weâ€™re building on what we learned previously, filling in the gaps and unknowns. We are coming to a new understanding, with these new tools, of how to create the front end at scale: Design Systems.</p>\n<p>We want isolated components that we can reuse, styles that donâ€™t conflict, and an easy authoring experience.</p>\n<p>At a high level, we know that a component needs to be three things:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>â€” easy to reason about</li>\n<li>â€” context agnostic</li>\n<li>â€” independent and isolated</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Our theory of components should be mostly applicable regardless of our tools. What works for one project may not work for another. But when you find things that donâ€™t work, gaps in our knowledge, that doesnâ€™t mean the whole theory is broken.</p>\n<p>We are experimenting with this theory of components every day as we work. What we learn will add to the theory, help us move forward, and create even better tools to improve our work. Searching for new solutions might even propel us forward so far we have as many new questions as answers. As we work together today and tomorrow and in the months and years to come, keep thinking beyond todayâ€™s understanding of the world, and on to tomorrowâ€™s.</p>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<p><em>Did you take notes during this talk? Share them with me and Iâ€™ll share them here!</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.prototypr.io/official-sketchnotes-from-clarity-conference-2017-f3ecae9ff105\">Official Sketchnotes</a> by <a href=\"https://twitter.com/cindyjchang\">Cindy Chang</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://sketchbookpages.tumblr.com/post/168232032192/sketchnotes-on-design-systems-28-29-november-2017\">sketchnotes by NÃ¡dia</a></li>\n<li>kudos on Twitter from <a href=\"https://twitter.com/i/web/status/1053014431637131264\">Christiano</a>, </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1JWoKHp9Mis&list=PL4CMETp4gcvMWLqdQlz5gl2GerF2WH7RU\">Recap Video</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Resources</h2>\n<h3>Books</h3>\n<p>These books inspired the science story in my talk. <em>Black Holes Blues</em> especially is the best book I have read in a long time. I highly recommend it!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://amzn.to/2BrXlHc\">Janna Levin, Black Hole Blues</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://amzn.to/2hZlEnF\">Kip Thorne, Black Holes &#x26; Time Warps</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://amzn.to/2k6TMSw\">Thomas Levenson, The Hunt for Vulcan</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://amzn.to/2AhlRuM\">David Baron, American Eclipse</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Science Links</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/gravitational-waves-even-more-ancient-black-hole-collisions-180963530/\">Hear the sound of two black holes colliding! smithsonianmag.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.sciencemag.org/news/2016/12/ripples-spacetime-sciences-2016-breakthrough-year\">Ripples in spacetime: Scienceâ€™s 2016 Breakthrough of the Year, sciencemag.org</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://phys.org/news/2017-09-ligo-virgo-observatories-black-hole.html\">LIGO and Virgo observatories detect gravitational wave signals from black hole collision, phys.org</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.economist.com/news/science-and-technology/21679172-century-ago-albert-einstein-changed-way-humans-saw-universe-his-work\">The most beautiful theory, economist.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.mathouriste.eu/Obs_Paris/Le_Verrier/Le%20Verrier.html\">Happy Bicentennial, Mr. Le Verrier, mathouriste.eu</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.oddsalon.com/jan-2-1860-the-discovery-of-planet-vulcan/\">Jan 2, 1860, the Discovery of Planet Vulcan, oddsalon.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.brainpickings.org/2016/11/29/janna-levin-black-hole-blues-science/\">Janna Levin on Black Hole Blues, brainpickings.org</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Tech Links</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/suitcss/suit/blob/master/doc/components.md#styling-dependencies\">SUIT CSS Styling dependencies</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.didoo.net/to-bem-or-not-to-bem/10__interview-with--mark__dalgleish.html\">Interview with Mark Dalgleish, didoo.net</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://markdalgleish.github.io/presentation-first-class-styles/\">Mark Dalgleish, First Class Styles presentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://medium.com/@didoo/let-there-be-peace-on-css-8b26829f1be0\">Let There Be Peace on CSS, didoo.net</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Credits</h2>\n<p>Slide design, color palette, and illustrations by the talented and lovely <a href=\"http://ainsleywagoner.com/\">Ainsley Wagoner</a>.</p>\n<p>The beautiful typeface is <a href=\"https://klim.co.nz/retail-fonts/tiempos-text/\">Klim Foundryâ€™s Tiempos Text and Headline</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"A Working Theory of Components","date":"November 27, 2017","conf":"ClarityConf"}}},"pageContext":{}}